        <h4>Seminars </h4>
        <p><a href="/seminars/shop-seminar-index.shtml" class="tableheader">Back to SEMINARS
            index</a></p>
        <h3>2014 Trial Skills College<br />
        </h3>
        <p>February 7–8, 2014 / University of Oregon Law School, Eugene<a href="http://www.hallmarkinns.com/index.asp?property=3&amp;rec_id=38" target="_blank"><br />
          </a>Co-sponsored by the University of Oregon Law School and OCDLA</p>
        <p><a href="https://www.ocdla.org/cart/seminarregister_newocdla.cfm?i=1388"><img src="/images/images-buttons/icon-registernow2.jpg" width="200" height="46" /></a><br />
        </p>
        <p>An<strong> intensive two-day training </strong>focusing on voir dire, opening statements, direct-examination, cross-examination and closing argument.</p>
        <p><img src="/images/images-seminars/trialskills/thuemmel_participant.jpg" width="182" height="241" class="imgLeft" />The program  trains trial lawyers in the learn-by-doing approach in a controlled non-threatening environment. The training  will significantly advance your skills and confidence as a trial lawyer, no matter your experience level. </p>
        <p><strong>Enrollment is limited to thirty-two participants</strong> who will selected from around the state to ensure geographic diversity. Using a prepared case students received in advance, the program will include <strong>lectures</strong>, <strong>demonstrations</strong>, and small<strong> group exercises </strong>that will include actual voir dire, cross-examination and closing argument. Volunteers will<strong></strong> play the part of key witnesses and jurors, further adding to the real-life feel of the trial  experience. The exercises are <strong>videotaped</strong> and then individually <strong>critiqued</strong> by an instructor during private meetings with participants.</p>
        <p><strong><img src="/images/images-seminars/trialskills/martha_spinhirne_200_rgb.jpg" width="200" height="150" class="imgRight" />Registratration (deadline January 13)<br />
        </strong><span class="style2"><span class="style9"><strong>Register online</strong>, and also <strong>send</strong> <strong>an email to </strong><a href="mailto:info@ocdla.org">info@ocdla.org</a> that includes the number of years you have practiced and the number of trials you have done  (this information is used for group placement purposes)</span></span>.</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
